These areas encompasse private lands, other governmental agency lands, and may contain National Forest System lands within the proclaimed boundaries of another administrative unit. All National Forest System lands fall within one and only one Administrative Forest Area. This map service provides display, identification, and analysis tools for determining current boundary information for Forest Service managers, GIS Specialists, and others. This map service is symbolized with a light green fill and a darker green outline. Labeling for each administrative unit starts at 1:10,000,000.</dct:description>         <dcat:keyword>region</dcat:keyword>         <dcat:keyword>forest number</dcat:keyword>
